      <hedline>
        <hl1>Carter's Papers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Andy Buck letter on R W Apple Jr article on PBS special Debating Our Destiny holds no credible documentary about presidential debates can omit mention of briefing papers stolen from Jimmy Carter's 1980 campaign that later turned up in Ronald Reagan's files (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>No credible documentary about presidential debates can omit a mention of the briefing papers that were stolen from Jimmy Carter's 1980 campaign and later turned up in the files of his opponent, Ronald Reagan.</p>
        <p>If Jim Lehrer, the host of the PBS special ''Debating Our Destiny,'' does not believe that any materials were ever pilfered, it was still irresponsible not to even mention a defining memory of the 1980 debate.</p>
        <p>ANDY BUCK  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
